how many\nsimilarities to the properties of local normal and high-z star forming\ngalaxies. Our findings strongly suggest that rapid evolution in the properties\nof the star forming regions of luminous infrared galaxies is likely to have\noccurred in the last 5 billion years.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 10 Jan 2014 12:13:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-18"}
